What are Lists
List is a data type where you can store multiple items under 1 name. More technically, lists act like dynamic arrays which means you can add more items on the fly.

Array Vs Lists:
Fixed Vs Dynamic Size
Convenience -> Hetrogeneous
Speed of Execution: Low as compared to array
Memory: More memory occupied than array

Characterstics of a List-
Ordered
Changeble/Mutable
Hetrogeneous
Can have duplicates
are dynamic
can be nested
items can be accessed
can contain any kind of objects in python


Disadvantages of Python Lists
Slow
Risky usage
eats up more memory


a = [1,2,3]
b = a

print(a)
print(b)

a.append(4)
print(a)
print(b)
Above code also modifies b value 2nd time
# lists are mutable

a = [1,2,3]
b = a.copy()

print(a)
print(b)

a.append(4)
print(a)
print(b)

# lists are mutable